paragraph.text:
to systematically integrate and coordinate efforts to prevent and respond to discrimination and
			 violence against LGBT people internationally into United States foreign
			 policy;

to support and build local capacity in countries  around the world, including of governments at all
			 levels and nongovernmental organizations, to prevent and respond to
			 discrimination and violence against LGBT people internationally;

to employ a multisectoral approach to preventing and responding to discrimination and violence
			 against LGBT people internationally, including activities in the
			 economic, education, health, nutrition, legal, and judicial sectors;

to work at all levels, from the individual to the family, community, local, national, and
			 international levels, to prevent and respond to discrimination and
			 violence against LGBT people internationally;

to ensure that international efforts to combat HIV/AIDS take all appropriate measures to support
			 at-risk communities, including LGBT persons, and to create enabling legal
			 environments for these communities;

subparagraph.text:
shall represent the United States in diplomatic matters relevant to the human rights of LGBT
			 people, including discrimination and violence against LGBT people
			 internationally;

subsection.text:

  Section 116(d) (
  22 U.S.C. 2151n(d)
) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 is amended—
